=head2 isbad

=for sig

  Signature: (a(); int [o]b())

=for ref

Returns a binary mask indicating which values of
the input are bad values

Returns a 1 if the value is bad, 0 otherwise.
Similar to L<isfinite|PDL::Math/isfinite>.

=for example

 $a = pdl(1,2,3);
 $a->badflag(1);
